stuff goes on backstage.

00:02:12.730 --> 00:02:15.610 align:middle line:84%
There are aspects to reality
that are not necessarily

00:02:15.610 --> 00:02:18.490 align:middle line:84%
reflected in the materialistic--
in the physical world

00:02:18.490 --> 00:02:21.010 align:middle line:84%
that we believe we
inhabit exclusively.

00:02:21.010 --> 00:02:24.130 align:middle line:10%
So this took the form
of an abiding interest

00:02:24.130 --> 00:02:26.260 align:middle line:10%
in various things
that our culture

00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:28.700 align:middle line:10%
considered to be
outside the norm,

00:02:28.700 --> 00:02:31.750 align:middle line:10%
became very involved in UFO
research over the years,

00:02:31.750 --> 00:02:34.810 align:middle line:10%
starting, actually, way
back in the early days

00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:37.055 align:middle line:10%
when it was not a
controversial topic.

00:02:37.055 --> 00:02:38.680 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Would you
explain that again?

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:39.722 align:middle line:90%
>>DRASIN: Well, back in--

00:02:39.722 --> 00:02:42.343 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What days-- what
era are you talking about?

00:02:42.343 --> 00:02:44.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: I'm talking
about the 1940s and '50S

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:44.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:02:44.650 --> 00:02:45.400 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:02:45.400 --> 00:02:45.610 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:02:45.610 --> 00:02:46.652 align:middle line:90%
>>DRASIN: I'm an old guy.

00:02:46.652 --> 00:02:48.020 align:middle line:90%
I was born in '42.

00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:53.980 align:middle line:84%
So I don't quite remember
Roswell, but, at that time,

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:58.240 align:middle line:84%
I do remember listening to a
radio broadcast every evening,

00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.360 align:middle line:84%
a mainstream New
York news commentator

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:04.090 align:middle line:84%
named Frank Edwards,
and he would give UFO

00:03:04.090 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:84%
sighting and landing
reports, which

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:11.270 align:middle line:84%
were a perfectly acceptable
realm of discussion

00:03:11.270 --> 00:03:12.070 align:middle line:90%
at that time--

00:03:12.070 --> 00:03:12.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:12.870 --> 00:03:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: --before the curtain
came down in the 1950s.

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:18.920 align:middle line:84%
And it became an
object of ridicule.

00:03:18.920 --> 00:03:19.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:22.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: So I was very
intrigued with that.

00:03:22.270 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
And that was, for me,
another example of what

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:26.255 align:middle line:90%
goes on backstage.

00:03:26.255 --> 00:03:27.880 align:middle line:84%
Actually, as you're
talking about that,

00:03:27.880 --> 00:03:31.790 align:middle line:84%
I remember as a news
anchor in the early 1980s,

00:03:31.790 --> 00:03:34.180 align:middle line:84%
we would have this stuff
come across the wire,

00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:37.930 align:middle line:84%
across writers and such AP,
where there had been a sighting

00:03:37.930 --> 00:03:40.450 align:middle line:84%
and the police were called,
and the whole town was

00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:42.010 align:middle line:90%
aware of what had gone on.

00:03:42.010 --> 00:03:44.168 align:middle line:90%
And I was always warned, no.

00:03:44.168 --> 00:03:45.460 align:middle line:90%
I tried to write stories on it.

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:48.260 align:middle line:84%
They always told me we don't
do that, toss them out.

00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:50.260 align:middle line:90%
And so, they never made it on.

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
And that was part
of that repression

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:52.630 align:middle line:90%
you're talking about.

00:03:52.630 --> 00:03:54.140 align:middle line:84%
It's not as though
it's not happening,

00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:56.307 align:middle line:84%
and it's not as though the
news stations don't know.

00:03:56.307 --> 00:03:58.870 align:middle line:84%
They won't allow you
to know, us to know.

00:03:58.870 --> 00:03:59.770 align:middle line:90%
So, continue on.

00:03:59.770 --> 00:04:00.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: Yeah,
and of course, we

00:04:00.580 --> 00:04:02.038 align:middle line:84%
know that's going
on today as well.

00:04:02.038 --> 00:04:05.980 align:middle line:84%
There's this whole battle
between the disclosure elements

00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:10.690 align:middle line:84%
in the armed forces now as well
and the old guard as it were.

00:04:10.690 --> 00:04:14.590 align:middle line:84%
And those of us who are
really interested in bringing

00:04:14.590 --> 00:04:19.120 align:middle line:84%
the hidden, together
with the obvious,

00:04:19.120 --> 00:04:21.579 align:middle line:84%
are following this
very, very closely.

00:04:21.579 --> 00:04:25.240 align:middle line:84%
And I think the question
of a so-called afterlife

00:04:25.240 --> 00:04:28.670 align:middle line:84%
is part of this bigger
picture of disclosure.

00:04:28.670 --> 00:04:29.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:29.470 --> 00:04:31.750 align:middle line:84%
In your book, "The New
Science of the Afterlife,"

00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:34.300 align:middle line:84%
which I loved because you
get right to the point.

00:04:34.300 --> 00:04:36.730 align:middle line:84%
But I love the fact
you're so in the face

00:04:36.730 --> 00:04:38.440 align:middle line:84%
with some of the
statements you made.

00:04:38.440 --> 00:04:40.890 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I'm going to
bring a couple of them up.

00:04:40.890 --> 00:04:44.350 align:middle line:84%
I was writing my
little notes-- love it.

00:04:44.350 --> 00:04:47.230 align:middle line:84%
Because you just don't
put up with fools anymore.

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:48.880 align:middle line:90%
You reach that point in life.

00:04:48.880 --> 00:04:51.460 align:middle line:84%
And basically, you're
saying the big block

00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:54.760 align:middle line:84%
to our understanding
of the nature of life

00:04:54.760 --> 00:04:58.510 align:middle line:84%
and reality has been
scientific materialism.

00:04:58.510 --> 00:05:02.890 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, you're
using a materialistic approach

00:05:02.890 --> 00:05:04.480 align:middle line:90%
because that's where we live.

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:05.530 align:middle line:90%
We live in that world.

00:05:05.530 --> 00:05:09.640 align:middle line:84%
You're using that to help
us understand the invisible.

00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: Well,
yes, I think it's

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:14.590 align:middle line:84%
important to bring in as
much physical evidence

00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:17.295 align:middle line:84%
of the metaphysical as
we can get our hands on.

00:05:17.295 --> 00:05:18.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:05:18.170 --> 00:05:19.878 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: Instrumental
transcommunication

00:05:19.878 --> 00:05:20.990 align:middle line:90%
is one aspect of that.

00:05:20.990 --> 00:05:22.698 align:middle line:84%
That is communication
from the other side

00:05:22.698 --> 00:05:23.930 align:middle line:90%
through modern electronics.

00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:26.450 align:middle line:84%
But anything that
brings the unfamiliar

00:05:26.450 --> 00:05:29.675 align:middle line:84%
into the realm of the
familiar is a bridge builder--

00:05:29.675 --> 00:05:30.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: --for
people's awareness.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:33.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, and those
are the two documentaries

00:05:33.420 --> 00:05:35.462 align:middle line:84%
that are going to be
focusing on in a little bit,

00:05:35.462 --> 00:05:37.880 align:middle line:84%
calling Earth, which is
that technology, and then

00:05:37.880 --> 00:05:39.745 align:middle line:90%
the famous "Scole.

00:05:39.745 --> 00:05:41.120 align:middle line:84%
The Afterlife
Experiment" is what

00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:42.860 align:middle line:84%
you call the video,
but the famous Scole

00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:46.413 align:middle line:84%
experiments out of England,
which were just phenomenal.

00:05:46.413 --> 00:05:47.580 align:middle line:90%
You did a great job on that.

00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:48.590 align:middle line:90%
So let's look back--

00:05:48.590 --> 00:05:51.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DRASIN: I want to give
credit to my co-producer,

00:05:51.410 --> 00:05:54.140 align:middle line:84%
